# Token Discipline (Always)

Goal: stop ~1M-token chats. Curated vault beats raw repo.

## Do

1. Read `docs/knowledge/00_HOME.md` then `15_MEMORY/Current-Context.md` first
2. Open only the feature / arch / DB / API notes for this task
3. Open only source files you will change or must verify
4. Prefer vault update over “read everything to be safe”
5. Keep replies short (caveman). No long restating of the task

## Do not

- Scan the entire repository unless user explicitly requests
- Glob/grep the whole tree “for context” when Home/Feature note already points to files
- Dump large file trees, full logs, or multi-file pastes into the reply
- Load fat archived AGENTS or `99_ARCHIVE/` unless migrating history
- Expand always-on rules with essays — keep rules short

## If stuck

Missing fact → create/update the right vault note, then continue. Do not compensate with bigger context windows.
